{"lemma":"خِيَمُ","slug":"خِيَمُ","root":"خ.#.م","root_slug":"خ-_-م","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-_-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n11900","n11904","n11905"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tent"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tarpaulin"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"arbor, bower"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pavilion"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Frequently thought to be a foreign word, in Jeffery’s words even “obviously not Arabic”. In this case most likely borrowed from Old South Arabian, from which source also Ge'ez ኀይመት (ḫäymät), Tigre ሓይመት (ḥaymät), Amharic ሃይመት (haymät). This could be countered with Ugaritic 𐎃𐎎𐎚 (ḫmt, “tent”) (attested multiple times), Ugaritic 𐎃𐎎𐎐 (ḫmn, “chapel, small temple”), Imperial Aramaic 𐡇𐡌𐡍 (ḥmn, “altar, chapel”), Hebrew חַמָּן (ḥammān, “altar, chapel”) – with a small probability related to Egyptian ḫꜣwt (“altar, altar chamber”) –, Ugaritic 𐎃𐎊𐎎 (ḫym, “canopy, baldachin”) – possibly related to Akkadian 𒌆𒄩𒁍𒌝 (^(TUG₂).ḪA.BU.UM), 𒌆𒄩𒌝 (^(TUG₂).ḪA.UM /⁠ḫaʾum, ḫawum⁠/, “a kind of covering cloth”).\nCompare also Kabyle taxxamt, taxyamt, axxam, axyam, this and equivalent words in other Berber languages meaning “tent” foremostly, and “cabin, chamber, room”, reconstructed for Proto-Berber rather than deemed borrowed from Arabic."},"ipa":["/xaj.ma/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n11900","headword_ar":"خيّم","root":"xym","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taxoyiymN","text_ar":"تَخْيِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) [originally]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He pitched his tent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rfD","text_ar":"رفض"},{"kind":"text","text":";) [like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txy~m","text_ar":"تخيّم"},{"kind":"text","text":": and hence, ―         -b2- ]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He remained, stayed, dwelt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place; (S, Msb, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xAm","text_ar":"خام","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaxiymu","text_ar":"يَخِيمُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": whence, in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahu Alr~ijaAlu qiyaAmFA","text_ar":"لَهُ الرِّجَالُ قِيَامًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^aHab~a A^ano yasotaxiyma","text_ar":"مَنْ اَحَبَّ اَنْ يَسْتَخِيمَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Whoso loveth that men should remain before him standing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; as some relate it; but others relate it differently, saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasotaxim~a","text_ar":"يَسْتَخِمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasotajim~a","text_ar":"يَسْتَجِمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as mentioned before [in arts."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xm","text_ar":"خم"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jm","text_ar":"جم"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He alighted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"descended and stopped"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sojourned"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in a place; as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~afa","text_ar":"خَيَّفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (JK in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xyf","text_ar":"خيف"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xy~m AlwaHo$iY~u fiY kinaAsihi","text_ar":"خيّم الوَحْشِىُّ فِى كِنَاسِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wild animal remained in his covert, not quitting it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~amati Alr~aAy^iHapu","text_ar":"خَيَّمَتِ الرَّايِحَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~iyHu AlT~ay~ibapu","text_ar":"الرِّيحُ الطَّيِّبَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (JK,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The odour,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sweet odour, remained;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"txmy~t","text_ar":"تخميّت","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K, TA;) in a garment, (JK, K, TA,) and in a place. (TA.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xay~amuwA","text_ar":"خَيَّمُوا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They entered into a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (JK, K.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xy~mhu","text_ar":"خيّمهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made it like a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomap","text_ar":"خَيْمَة"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA.) ―         -b2-  See also 4. ―         -b3-  Also (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He covered it with a thing in order that its odour might cling to it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Msb","K","TA","JK"]},{"entry_id":"n11904","headword_ar":"خَيْمٌ","root":"xym","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayomapN","text_ar":"خَيْمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in three places."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n11905","headword_ar":"خِيمٌ","root":"xym","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Natural,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"innate, dispositions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tempers"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, S, M, K:) a Persian word, arabicized: (TA:) having no sing. (S, K) of its own radical letters: (S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"largeness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"liberality, of disposition:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, TA:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"original,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"primary, state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSol","text_ar":"اَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":", of the soul, or mind. (TA.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa kariymu Alxiymi","text_ar":"هُوَ كَرِيمُ الخِيمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is generous in respect of natural dispositions"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversified wavy marks, streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firinod","text_ar":"فِرِنْد"},{"kind":"text","text":", of a sword. (K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoDN","text_ar":"حَمْضٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"kind of plants called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamoD","text_ar":"حَمْض"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","K","JK"]}]}}